How to compile

Go to the directory (Project Part-1) containing the files
main.cpp, UI.h, UI.cpp, Cache.h, Cache.cpp, Memory.h, Memory.cpp

write the command
g++ *.h *.cpp -o <name of output file>

This will generate the binary.



To run

Go to the directory (Project Part-1) containing the binary
./<name of binary> -c<capacity> -b<blocksize> -a<associativity> -r<replacement policy> -v<verbose> <input_trace>
All options except the input_trace have default values, so they are optional.
The default values are capacity = 8k, blocksize = 16bytes, associativity = 4, replacement policy = LRU & verbose disabled.


